column3: As discussed on IRC, Travis failure unrelated.\n

Rerun and archived failure here:

```
test count = ../../../src/secp256k1/src/tests.c64
random seed = 803fa67dcab64b4b14a4c0089a34e7b6
:393: test condition failed: ((~x[m][shift]) << (64 - (1 << usebits))) == 0
```
@MarcoFalke's failure is a randomness test in libsecp256k1 that has a very low (but still too high) false positive rate.\n
